"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-news-assos-releases-dollar7000-skin-suit-to-the-general-public-ahead-of-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  The Fenoq 'kit' involves custom tailoring, and overshoes too  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  Assos, the high-end Swiss cycling clothing manufacturer, has made its top-end chronosuit (or skinsuit to use the common parlance) available to purchase by the public for the first time.\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swiss_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Swiss cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swiss_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swiss_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The brand says the suit is 'completely bespoke to athletes on the road to Paris 24'.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We assume the skinsuit has been provided to Assos athletes or sponsored teams for some time but is now being made available to purchase via the brand's website.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The skinsuit, which is named the Fenoq, will be available as a single suit starting at \\u00a32,180 / $2,761.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or as a 'pack' which includes a 100% custom garment and includes overshoes.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The starting price for this option will be a whopping \\u00a35,670/ $7,040  On the Fenoq page on the brand's website, two suit options are listed.\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first is the Feno suit which is custom-made and designed for Time Trial use.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_trial\", \"score\": 0.9019009418271391, \"rank\": 0.10876921580102675, \"text\": \"Time Trial\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_trial\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_trial\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Assos says the suit has been engineered and tested in the wind tunnel as well as at UCI WorldTour races.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999996081670218, \"rank\": 3.9183297289283283e-07, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We understand this option to be a highly optimised but off-the-peg skinsuit which starts at \\u00a32,710.\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Fenoq pack jumps up in price and is a completely bespoke offering if you will, with the skinsuit itself being 100% custom.\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Assos says the suit is wind tunnel data and track test certified.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that the fabric features a skinGrip finish, twinDeck sleeves and a back panel.\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Overshoes are also included to the tune of \\u00a35,670 / $7,040There is not an option to add the skinsuit to your basket and purchase, instead interested customers are asked to fill out a form registering their interest.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The most cutting-edge, aero-optimised skinsuits still seem to be reserved for time trials and on the track, though race suits are commonplace on the road now.\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fastest skin suits still take things one step further.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Optimised and custom skin suits are nothing new but they are often not easy to find information on and difficult to purchase, especially when worn by national teams on the track for example.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, for track races, any equipment used at the Olympic games must have been commercially available from January 1st of the Olympic year per UCI article 1.3.006, it's just not openly advertised as you might expect.\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2426, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999996081670218, \"rank\": 3.9183297289283283e-07, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We would imagine if a nation thinks they have the fastest skinsuit around they are not likely to openly advertise it in the run-up to an Olympic year.\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some skinsuits have rocked the boat over the last few years and have even been rendered unusable thanks to shifting UCI regulations.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2768, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999996081670218, \"rank\": 3.9183297289283283e-07, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022 we covered theVorteq skinsuit that Simon Yates usedto win a Giro TT stage.\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2828, \"end\": 2839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simon_Yates_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9846717166986766, \"rank\": 0.015566340078741626, \"text\": \"Simon Yates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simon_Yates_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simon_Yates_(cyclist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That particular skinsuit was priced at \\u00a32,750 / $3,483 a little shy of the Assos Fenoq though Vorteq does list Paris Edition discipline-specific skinsuits starting from \\u00a33,000 / $3,800  The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 3156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2979, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.485428985224417e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some skinsuits also fell foul of UCI rules several years ago, with thecontroversial Team Sky Castelli body paint skinsuitfeaturing 'vortex dimples' or grooved fabric to aid airflow falling outside of UCI regulations.\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3191, \"end\": 3194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999996081670218, \"rank\": 3.9183297289283283e-07, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}, {\"begin\": 3242, \"end\": 3250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\"}, {\"begin\": 3251, \"end\": 3259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Castelli\", \"score\": 0.999986238843674, \"rank\": 1.376134257914877e-05, \"text\": \"Castelli\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Castelli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Castelli\"}, {\"begin\": 3358, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999996081670218, \"rank\": 3.9183297289283283e-07, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Endura / Drag 2 Zero skinsuit also fell outside the rules due to the 'textured material' the suit used.\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3379, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Endura-D_engine\", \"score\": 0.9999999996953193, \"rank\": 1.1469618129205241e-10, \"text\": \"Endura\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Endura-D_engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Endura-D_engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other competitors to the Assos offering right now are perhaps the WattShop - Custom labs custom skin suit that comes in at \\u00a32,500 / $3,167 with a custom fitting and aero testing included.\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Santini also offers its Viper skinsuit which is said to be used by Trek Segafredo and the Australia National cycling team, Santini will provide you with a quote if you are interested in one.\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3744, \"end\": 3753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massimo_Zanetti_Beverage_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Segafredo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massimo_Zanetti_Beverage_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massimo_Zanetti_Beverage_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 3762, \"end\": 3771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998160975561234, \"rank\": 0.00017967451970610446, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We expect to see more equipment from clothing to road and track equipment quietly appear in the run-up to the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 3991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As mentioned, some of it is not openly shouted about but we will be doing our best to spot it when it does appear.\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's always exciting to spot new and cutting-edge equipment in an Olympic year as manufacturers strive to provide athletes with the very best.\", \"from\": 4107, \"to\": 4249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The track bike narrative in the run-up to Paris 24 has been interesting to follow with a range of outlandish designs appearing as the aero boundaries are pushed.\", \"from\": 4251, \"to\": 4412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thewild-looking Stromm track bikeas well asToot Racing offeringsare just two bikes that have caught the eye so far.\", \"from\": 4413, \"to\": 4528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom joined the Cyclingnews team in late 2022 as a tech writer.\", \"from\": 4532, \"to\": 4594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4547, \"end\": 4558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite having a degree in English Literature he has spent his entire working life in the cycling industry in one form or another.\", \"from\": 4595, \"to\": 4725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has over 10 years of experience as a qualified mechanic, with the last five years before joining Cyclingnews being spent running an independent workshop.\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4826, \"end\": 4837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means he is just as happy tinkering away in the garage as he is out on the road bike, and he is not afraid to pull a bike apart or get hands-on with it when testing to really see what it's made of.\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 5085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has ridden and raced bikes from an early age up to a national level on the road and track, and has ridden and competed in most disciplines.\", \"from\": 5089, \"to\": 5231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has a keen eye for pro-team tech and enjoys spotting new or interesting components in the wild.\", \"from\": 5232, \"to\": 5330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During his time at Cyclingnews, Tom has already interviewed some of the sport's biggest names including Mathieu van der Poel, Tadej Poga\\u010dar and Alberto Contador.\", \"from\": 5331, \"to\": 5492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5350, \"end\": 5361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}, {\"begin\": 5435, \"end\": 5455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}, {\"begin\": 5457, \"end\": 5470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9999999996084625, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tadej Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}, {\"begin\": 5475, \"end\": 5482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alberto_Giacometti\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.123346369801009e-12, \"text\": \"Alberto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alberto_Giacometti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alberto_Giacometti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's also covered various launches from brands such as Pinarello, Ridley, Specialized and more, tackled the Roubaix Challenge sportive aboard his own rim-brake Cannondale SuperSix Evo, tested over 20 aero helmets in the wind tunnel, and has created helpful in-depth buying advice relating to countless categories from torque wrenches to winter clothing.\", \"from\": 5493, \"to\": 5846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5548, \"end\": 5557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinarello\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pinarello\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinarello\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pinarello\"}, {\"begin\": 5653, \"end\": 5663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannondale_station\", \"score\": 0.8933320588381508, \"rank\": 0.11940458209956352, \"text\": \"Cannondale\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannondale_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannondale_station\"}, {\"begin\": 5673, \"end\": 5676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitsubishi_Lancer_Evolution\", \"score\": 0.9999992866339924, \"rank\": 7.133544090008533e-07, \"text\": \"Evo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitsubishi_Lancer_Evolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mitsubishi_Lancer_Evolution\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cyclingnews is part of Future plc, an international media group and leading digital publisher.Visit our corporate site.\", \"from\": 5848, \"to\": 5967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5848, \"end\": 5859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}, {\"begin\": 5871, \"end\": 5881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Future plc\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Future Publishing Limited Quay House, The Ambury, Bath BA1 1UA.\", \"from\": 5969, \"to\": 6034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5971, \"end\": 5988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.97923790888672e-15, \"text\": \"Future Publishing\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\"}, {\"begin\": 6002, \"end\": 6007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"score\": 0.9999999229808084, \"rank\": 4.3802668044668645e-08, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 6035, \"to\": 6055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"England and Wales company registration number 2008885.\", \"from\": 6056, \"to\": 6110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6056, \"end\": 6063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9419612144853179, \"rank\": 0.060015653768089317, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6068, \"end\": 6073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\", \"score\": 0.5915554433335959, \"rank\": 0.690457670228523, \"text\": \"Wales\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please login or signup to comment  Please wait...\", \"from\": 6112, \"to\": 6161, \"entities\": []}]}"